cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with unsupervised feature learning using convolutional neural networks for computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of discriminative learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks also makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method on image matching tasks, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
